          <h2>Change Tracking — Every iteration is impact-aware</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="delta-intro">
        <p>Traditional AI coding ("vibe coding") fixes the code but forgets the design doc, the API spec, and the test cases. Over time, documentation drifts from reality and becomes useless. OpenLogos solves this with a <strong>structured delta workflow</strong> — every change, no matter how small, must evaluate its ripple effect across the entire artifact chain.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="delta-workflow">
        <div class="dw-step"><div class="dw-num">1</div><div class="dw-text"><strong>proposal.md</strong><span>Reason, type, impact scope, summary</span></div></div>
        <div class="dw-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="dw-step"><div class="dw-num">2</div><div class="dw-text"><strong>tasks.md</strong><span>Phase-based task checklist</span></div></div>
        <div class="dw-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="dw-step"><div class="dw-num">3</div><div class="dw-text"><strong>Delta files</strong><span>Produce changes per task</span></div></div>
        <div class="dw-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="dw-step"><div class="dw-num">4</div><div class="dw-text"><strong>Merge</strong><span><code>openlogos merge</code></span></div></div>
        <div class="dw-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="dw-step"><div class="dw-num">5</div><div class="dw-text"><strong>Code + Test</strong><span>Implement &amp; verify</span></div></div>
        <div class="dw-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="dw-step"><div class="dw-num">6</div><div class="dw-text"><strong>Archive</strong><span>Close the proposal</span></div></div>
      </div>

